<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">Comments.</emphasis>
Based on its maculated wings, 
<taxonomicName authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[700,857,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[700,857,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">Bittacus cruzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[866,931,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[866,931,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
fits in the “group 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1838" box="[1145,1243,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis box="[1145,1243,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[151,468,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. Within the group, it shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[854,981,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis box="[854,981,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Byers" authorityYear="1965" box="[1039,1190,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1190,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">B. maculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the number of costal crossveins in the wings (one). However, the shape of the male epandrium suggests a closer relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,305,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi">
<emphasis box="[151,305,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">Bittacus cruzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Morgante" authorityYear="1967" box="[359,531,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boraceiensis">
<emphasis box="[359,531,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">B. boraceiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; both species present a medial actiniform process, but the subapical processes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Morgante" authorityYear="1967" box="[151,324,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boraceiensis">
<emphasis box="[151,324,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="308">B. boraceiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are absent in the new species, easily separating them.
</paragraph>
